  "text": "Expression of Nrp1 by MDA-MB-231 and MCF-7 cells was suppressed by Nrp1-targeted small interfering RNA (siRNA) transfection using oligonucleotides (Santa Cruz Biotechnology, Santa Cruz, CA) and Fugene-6 (Roche Biosciences, Palo Alto, CA) as a transfection reagent. MDA-MB-453 cells were transfected with pBLAST vector encoding the complete human Nrp1 sequence (Invivogen, San Diego, CA). Efficiency of transfection was tested by cell enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) and immunofluorescence analysis. Positive or negative magnetic sorting of Nrp1 þ cells was performed using anti-Nrp1 antibodies, as described [CITATION_1] .",
